openengsb-2.0.2 2012-03-30
-----------------------------------------

The 2.0.2 release of the OpenEngSB contains various minor bug fixes in it's internal, mostly via the upgrade of
the OpenEngSB framework. In addition we've upgraded bug-fix releases of CXF and Wicket. None of those fixes should
have any effect of your experiences with the OpenEngSB.

### Details
** Library Upgrade
    * [OPENENGSB-2864] - Upgrade to framework 2.4.3
    * [OPENENGSB-2865] - Upgrade docbkx version to 2.0.14
    * [OPENENGSB-2866] - Upgrade root to v32

** Task
    * [OPENENGSB-2863] - Release openengsb-2.0.2

### Known Issues
    * [OPENENGSB-1353] Jira Axis connector conflicts with openengsb-ports CXF


openengsb-2.0.1 2012-01-17
-----------------------------------------

Bugfix release upgrading openengsb-framework to 2.4.1. By this upgrade we've fixed the main problem that not
all artifacts are downloaded in offline mode. OpenEngSB 2.0.1 could be run in offline mode again.

### Details
** Library Upgrade
    * [OPENENGSB-2696] - Upgrade to framework-2.4.1

** Task
    * [OPENENGSB-2053] - Release openengsb-2.0.1

### Known Issues
    * [OPENENGSB-1353] Jira Axis connector conflicts with openengsb-ports CXF

openengsb-2.0.0 2012-01-12
-----------------------------------------

The final release 2.0.0 of the Open Engineering Service Bus comes with OpenEngSB Framework 2.4.0 including a varitie
of new features: A general possibility to handle OAuth, now allowing connectors to e.g. Facebook and Twitter; A set
of Karaf command line support (info, service, connector, domain); Implementation of the Engineering Database for 
version and storing models; A prototypic implementation of the Engineering Knoledge Base allowing to work with the
models of tools and query against them; Minor enhancements in the administration UI (coloring, bug-fixes, ...); Java 7
compability; Full filter chains for the implementation of the remoting part making it possible to configure encryption,
authentication, authorisation, and method calls quite easily; JPA support within the OpenEngSB; Possibility to create
and change connector instances in configuration files. In addition those releases bring the following new versions and
all their new features and bug fixes of the base tools to the OpenEngSB: Apache Karaf (2.2.5); Apache CXF (2.5.1),
Apache ActiveMQ (5.5.1), Drools (5.3.0.FINAL), Wicket (1.4.19). The OpenEngSB 2.0.0 comes with the following tools
and connectors: Binary Transformation Provider Factory (Smooks Binary Transform Provider Factory), 
Auditing (MemoryAuditing), Example (Example), Notification (Email), Appointment (Gcalendar), Contact (Gcontacts), 
Scm (Git), Issue (Github, Trac), Build (Maven), Test (Maven), Deploy (Maven), Report (Plain Text Report, ProM Report);
All of those connectors and domains had been adapted to the latest version of the framework.

